how much weight are you supposed to gain during pregancy i really dont want to gain to much weight what a drag it will be to get it off rule of thumb for a normal weight woman about pounds if you are overweight to begin with is fine or even none usually works out ok if you are eating regularly if underweight to start with is a good idea many women with gestational diabetes who follow their diet don't gain any more weight after their diagnosis and that seems to do nothing but good to the baby so what you eat and eating regularly are more important than how much weight you gain if you gain pounds likely it will be gone within a few weeks without dieting ask for a copy of the gestational diabetes diet and use it as a guideline it is a good diet for anyone who is pregnant Dieting Obesity Pregnancy Atkins Nutritional Approach Diabetes mellitus Binge eating disorder Coeliac disease Body mass index Anorexia nervosa Super Size Me Obstetrics Folic acid Adjustable gastric band Hypertension Breastfeeding Hamster Birth weight Childbirth Miscarriage Hyperglycemia Dialysis Cystic fibrosis South Beach diet Raw food diet Premature birth Sugar substitute Diabetes insipidus Vegetarianism Weight training Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Elephant Polycystic ovary syndrome Fasting Terri Schiavo Jennifer Lopez Human height Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Tocopherol Physical examination Omega-3 fatty acid Dick Gregory Oral contraceptive Weight Watchers Milk Weight loss Abortion debate Haemochromatosis Diabetic retinopathy Elvis and Me Low-carbohydrate diet Insulin resistance Vampire Cancer Osteoporosis Healthy eating Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Social rule Exercise Nutrition Diet soda Garfield Diabetes mellitus type 2 Calorie restriction Insulin Hypoglycemia Peter Singer Coffee Turner syndrome Androgen insensitivity syndrome Chlorpromazine Bodybuilding Weight Urinary incontinence Veganism Dietary fiber Body image Mario Diabetic nephropathy Byzantine coinage Sea Otter Oily fish The 